-- Siamgas to Raise $67 Million for Petrochemical Expansion, Kao Hoon Reports
-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 2010-11-25T01:41:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-25/siamgas-to-raise-67-million-for-petrochemical-expansion-kao-hoon-reports.html
Siamgas & Petrochemical Pcl, a Thai
supplier of liquefied petroleum gas, plans to raise about 2
billion baht ($66.5 million) by selling bonds and shares to fund
expansion, Kao Hoon reported, citing Deputy Managing Director
Jintana Kingkaew.  The company plans to acquire an LPG supplier in Malaysia to
boost overseas revenue following its expansion in China and
Vietnam, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
